## Why This Is Asked

Gauges expertise with containerized TLS, mTLS, and production-grade upgrade flows on RHCSA level. Checks practical config, SELinux scoping, and firewall integration in a realistic, scalable setup.

## Key Concepts

- Podman-based TLS termination in a container
- mTLS with CA and per-client certs
- OCSP stapling for performance
- systemd-based zero-downtime upgrade
- SELinux policy for nginx_t and cert access
- nftables rulecraft for 8443 and backend access
- upgrade/test strategy including revocation

## Code Example

```nginx
server {
  listen 8443 ssl;
  ssl_certificate /mnt/certs/server.crt;
  ssl_certificate_key /mnt/certs/server.key;
  ssl_client_certificate /mnt/certs/ca.crt;
  ssl_verify_client on;
  ssl_stapling on;
  location / {
    proxy_pass http://10.0.0.20:8080;
  }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would certificate revocation be handled and propagated to clients?
- How would you monitor upgrades and auto-recovery from a failed deployment?
